This can occur when Ant doesn't get HTTP_NOT_MODIFIED in the response headers. 
It then goes on to compare the timestamps, but should check that the local file
is younger _or_as_young_ as the remote file.  Suggest the following fix:
Lines 164-167
            if (httpConnection.getResponseCode()
                    == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_NOT_MODIFIED
                || (lastModified != 0 && hasTimestamp
                && timestamp > lastModified)) {
should be changed to
            if (httpConnection.getResponseCode()
                    == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_NOT_MODIFIED
                || (lastModified != 0 && hasTimestamp
                && timestamp >= lastModified)) {
